cess story insight innovation impact using mealsense™ to drive student participation makes sense insight innovation impact insight one of the challenges schools face in increasing free and reduced meal program participation is that many eligible parents often do not submit applications due to lack of awareness about the program misunderstanding of eligibility qualifications lack of time and the stigma associated with receiving free meals see our innovation innovation our proprietary mealsense™ program is a stepbystep process to increase free and reducedprice applications meal sense delivers integrated communication solutions to raise program awareness and keep it “topofmind” for parents while providing clear simple and easily accessible applications and information see our impact impact districts that implemented the aramark mealsense™ program experienced a  to  increase in free and reduced applications this means more students are receiving nutritious meals in order to perform their best throughout the day and districts are maximizing their federal reimbursements for school meal programs contact us patrick sandoval chefarea supervisor pflugerville independent school district pflugerville tx employee spotlight what i hope kids take away from our nutrition education program is that food is everchanging and food is extremely exciting and there’s such a vast array of different food out there healthy foods can be fun exciting and taste good walter doughty dir of nutrition and transportation waukegan public school district waukegan il partner focus aramark has been great in their presentation of meal planning and providing the menus for us within usda nutritional guidelines there’s a constant chance to make sure that everything is new and different and that they meet those guidelines that most of us wouldn’t be able to find more info on school districts explore our services there’s a lot more we do to make your school district an even better learning environment faciliti